{"parse":{"title":"Wetlands","pageid":14035,"wikitext":{"*":"{{infobox zone\n|faction=Contested\n|name=Wetlands\n|ss=The Green Belt.jpg\n|races={{Race|Human }} (7,500)<br />\n{{Race|Ironforge Dwarf }} (7,500)<br />\n{{Race|Night Elf }}{{Cata-inline}} <br />\n{{RaceIcon|Dragonmaw|Male|Small}}{{RaceIcon|Dragonmaw|Female|Small}} [[Orc]], [[Dragonmaw Clan|Dragonmaw]] (7,500)<br />\n{{Race|Dark Iron Dwarf }} (2,500)<br />\n{{Race|Red Dragonflight }}<br />\n{{RaceIconExt|Gnoll|Small}} [[Gnoll]]<br />\n{{Race|Murloc }}<br />\n|level=Scalable 25-60\n|loc=Northern [[Khaz Modan]]\n|affiliation=[[Alliance]]\n|pop= 25,000\n|capital=[[Menethil Harbor]] (12,000)\n|language=[[Common (language)|Common]], [[Dwarven]], [[Orcish|Orc]]\n|faith=[[Holy Light]]\n|resource=Ruins, safe harbor\n|source=''[[Lands of Conflict]]'' 79-80\n}}\n\nThe '''Wetlands''' is a large, wet zone below [[Stonewrought Dam]] and north of [[Loch Modan]], covered with small rivers, lakes, and ponds. Bordered on three sides by mountains, the Wetlands are open to the ocean to the west. Adventurers seeking a route to the Wetlands must either come through sieged [[Dun Algaz]] from Loch Modan or cross the damaged [[Thandol Span]] from [[Arathi Highlands]]. The northern slopes of the Wetlands are generally classed within the [[Khaz Mountains]].\n\nThe Wetlands is a vast, cold swamp. Mists cloak the ground, and the overcast sky makes the land a uniform gray. Many Ironforge strongholds once stood in this region, but war has reduced them to rubble. Wild creatures, murlocs, and renegade orcs now control the land. [[Menethil Harbor]], a city on the west coast, is the Alliance\u2019s only presence in this dreary region.<ref name=\"Lands of Conflict 17\">''[[Lands of Conflict]]'', pg. 17</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe Wetlands have been the site of many a battle through the times. Nestled among the [[Khaz Mountains]] and open to the ocean as it is, it is a prime location for invading forces. It was historically part of the original [[dwarven]] kingdom while the three tribes were united, but after the [[War of the Three Hammers]], it fell under control of the [[Wildhammer Clan]]. The Dark Irons invaded [[Grim Batol]] and almost succeeded in taking full control of it, but were driven back at the last minute. During the [[Second War]], the bastion finally fell prey to the invading orcs, most notably by those of the [[Dragonmaw Clan]]. \n\nAlthough the orcs took possession of Grim Batol for a time, they were subject to the wrath of the [[red dragonflight]] who, when freed of their enslavement from the orcs, destroyed their bases and burned their catapults, killing orcs en masse. The orcs who survived the onslaught fled south to the mountains, where they live to this day. Horde and Scourge forces devastated the Wetlands in the Second and Third Wars, forcing the Ironforge dwarves to retreat to Loch Modan and Dun Morogh.<ref name=\"Lands of Conflict 80\">''[[Lands of Conflict]]'', pg. 80</ref> \n\nGrim Batol is now under the control of the red dragonflight, who fiercely defend their lair from outsiders. Alliance forces have since established Menethil Harbor, but the area is still wild and untamed.<ref name=\"Lands of Conflict 80\">''[[Lands of Conflict]]'', pg. 80</ref> The dwarves and allied humans built the port city on an island in Baradin Bay, which they named after King [[Terenas Menethil II]] \u2014 [[Menethil Harbor]]. The Wetlands is a buffer zone between inhabited Khaz Modan and Scourge-infested Lordaeron.<ref name=\"Lands of Conflict 80\">''[[Lands of Conflict]]'', pg. 80</ref>\n\n{{Cata-section}}\nMenethil Harbor withstood the brunt of the effects of the [[Cataclysm]], the large city flooded by the high waters. The citizens have done what they can while maintaining a tenuous hold on the port, sandbagging areas and repairing others. It is hard to walk through the town without sloshing through deep pools. The docks are even damaged, though still functional. The Dark Iron dwarves have attempted to take advantage of the distraction, somehow infiltrating and holding [[Menethil Keep]], though this is ultimately short-lived.\n\nThe other major disaster to strike the Wetlands is the destruction of the [[Stonewrought Dam]] in [[Loch Modan]]. The waters of the loch plummeted into the marshes far below, not only flooding much of the surrounding area but also displacing several species unfamiliar to the zone, including [[threshadon]]s. Perhaps the only good to come of this is that the [[gnoll]]s have largely abandoned that southeastern portion.\n\nA host of new elementals have risen to swarm the now-unoccupied areas, including [[Direforge Hill]] and parts of [[Mosshide Fen]]. [[Whelgar's Excavation Site]] has been abandoned by the dwarves, fleeing from [[Living Fossil|skeletal raptors]] that now skulk through the dig site, though Whelgar himself has set up [[Whelgar's Retreat|camp]] nearby. Battles wage on a few fronts: the dwarves still fight at [[Dun Modr]], but now it has been revealed their fight has been with the [[Twilight's Hammer clan]] all along; and the gnolls and dark iron dwarves squabble over [[Saltspray Glen]]. A number of new [[dragonkin]] now inhabit the [[Green Belt]] as well.\n\nThere have been some Alliance gains, however. The largest of them is the addition of a new [[night elf]]-inspired [[Greenwarden's Grove|town]] built up around [[Rethiel the Greenwarden]]. A small dwarven camp has been established near Mosshide Fen and now even [[Fradd Swiftgear]] can boast an inn of his own.\n\n== Geography ==\nThe Wetlands is a large marsh, full of swampy pools and very little flora besides tall grasses and a scattering of trees. High mountains border the zone on every side but the west, which is open to the sea. Passes lead to [[Arathi Highlands]] in the north and [[Loch Modan]] to the southeast. Since the [[Cataclysm]] much of the southeast portion is flooded due to the destruction of the Stonewrought Dam, and Menethil Harbor is also flooded along the coast.\n\n== Travel ==\n=== Getting there ===\n[[File:Gryphon.png|right|Gryphon]]\n;{{Alliance Icon Small}} Alliance: From [[Ironforge]], run east towards [[Loch Modan]] and take the road in the Loch north through [[Dun Algaz]] and into the Wetlands. Or, take the boat from [[Theramore]] (for night elves and draenei).\n;{{Horde Icon Small}} Horde: From [[Hammerfall]] in the [[Arathi Highlands]], run south/southwest to the bottom of the zone.  Cross the ruined bridge.\n\n=== Flight Master locations ===\n:{{Alliance}} [[Dun Modr]] {{C-inline}}\n:{{Alliance}} [[Greenwarden's Grove]] {{C-inline}}\n:{{Alliance}} [[Menethil Harbor]]\n:{{Alliance}} [[Slabchisel's Survey]] {{C-inline}}\n:{{Alliance}} [[Whelgar's Retreat]] {{C-inline}}\n\n=== Boat locations ===\n:{{Alliance}} [[Menethil Harbor]] (''to [[Theramore Isle]], [[Dustwallow Marsh]]'')\n:{{Alliance}} [[Menethil Harbor]] (''to [[Valgarde]], [[Howling Fjord]]'') {{wotlk-inline}} required\n\n=== Adjacent regions ===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Zone Name || Faction || Level Range || Direction || {{Alliance}} Access || {{Horde}} Access\n|-\n| [[Arathi Highlands]]\n| {{Alliance}} {{Horde}}\n| 25-30 || North\n| By foot across [[Thandol Span]]; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Menethil Harbor]] to [[Refuge Pointe]]\n| By foot across [[Thandol Span]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Dun Morogh]]\n| {{Alliance}}\n| 1-10 || Southwest\n| [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Menethil Harbor]] to [[Ironforge]]\n| By foot south to [[Loch Modan]], then roughly east through [[South Gate Pass]]\n|-\n| [[Dustwallow Marsh]]\n| {{Alliance}} {{Horde}}\n| 35-40 || West across the ocean \n| Boat from [[Menethil Harbor]] to [[Theramore Isle]]\n| Boat from [[Menethil Harbor]] to [[Theramore Isle]] (Alliance transport, '''not recommended''')\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Howling Fjord]]{{wotlk-inline}}\n| {{Alliance}} {{Horde}}\n| 68-72 || Northwest across the ocean \n| Boat from [[Menethil Harbor]] to [[Valgarde]]\n| Boat from [[Menethil Harbor]] to [[Valgarde]] (Alliance transport, '''not recommended''')\n|-\n| [[Loch Modan]] || {{Alliance}}\n| 10-20 || Southeast\n| By foot via [[Dun Algaz]]; [[File:MiniIcon FlightMaster.png]] from [[Menethil Harbor]] or [[Slabchisel's Survey]] to [[Thelsamar]]\n| By foot via [[Dun Algaz]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Twilight Highlands]]{{c-inline}}\n| {{Alliance}} {{Horde}}\n| 84-85 || East\n| By foot east through [[Dragonmaw Gates]]\n| By foot east through [[Dragonmaw Gates]]\n|}\n\n== Inhabitants ==\n[[File:Beasts.png|right]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Classification !! Type\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" | [[Beast]]\n| [[Crab]]s\n|-\n| [[Crocolisk]]s\n|-\n| [[Raptor]]s\n|-\n| [[Shark]]s\n|-\n| [[Spider]]s\n|-\n| [[Threshadon]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Dragonkin]]\n| [[Dragonspawn]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Drake]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Whelp]]s\n|-\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Elemental]]\n| [[Bog Beast]]s\n|-\n| [[Earth Elemental]]s\n|-\n| [[Fire Elemental]]s\n|-\n| [[Lasher]]s\n|-\n| [[Water Elemental]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" |[[Humanoid]]\n| [[Dwarves]]\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Gnoll]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Murloc]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Orc]]s\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Uncategorized]]\n| [[Ooze]]s\n|-\n| [[Slime]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" |[[Undead]]\n| [[Ghost]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Living Fossil]]s\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| [[Skeleton]]s\n|}\n\n==Resources==\n[[File:Trade mining.png|right]]\n[[File:Trade herbalism.png|right]]\n[[File:Inv misc pelt wolf 01.png|right]]\n[[File:Trade fishing.png|right]]\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Source !! Item !! Skill Level\n|-\n| rowspan=\"8\" | [[Herbalism]]\n| {{item|icon=|Mageroyal}}\n| align=\"center\" | 50\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Briarthorn}}\n| align=\"center\" | 70\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Bruiseweed}}\n| align=\"center\" | 85\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Stranglekelp}}\n| align=\"center\" | 85\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Grave Moss}}\n| align=\"center\" | 105\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Wild Steelbloom}}\n| align=\"center\" | 115\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Kingsblood}}\n| align=\"center\" | 125\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Liferoot}}\n| align=\"center\" | 150\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Mining]]\n| {{item|icon=|Copper Ore}} from Copper Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 1\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Tin Ore}} from Tin Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 65\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Silver Ore}} from Silver Veins\n| align=\"center\" | 75\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Iron Ore}} from Iron Deposits\n| align=\"center\" | 125\n|}\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n! Source !! Item\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[Cloth]] (Drop)\n| {{item|icon=|Linen Cloth}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Wool Cloth}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Silk Cloth}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Skinning]]\n| {{item|icon=|Light Leather}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Medium Leather}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Heavy Leather}}\n|- class=\"alt\"\n| {{item|icon=|Black Whelp Scale}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[Fishing]] (Pools)\n| {{item|icon=|Firefin Snapper}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Oily Blackmouth}}\n|-\n| {{item|icon=|Sagefish}}\n|-\n| {{profIcon|Fishing}}[[Schooner Wreckage]]\n|}\n\n==Notable characters==\n{{main|Wetlands NPCs}}\n\nThe Wetlands are home to several characters of note. In Menethil Harbor, [[Captain Stoutfist]] sends promising young adventurers to end the threat of the [[Dragonmaw Clan]]. At Dun Modr, [[Rhag Garmason]] seeks to recover the besieged town from the dark iron dwarves. And in the Green Belt, the wise [[Rethiel the Greenwarden]] wishes to put an end to the gnoll incursion and the corruption of his lesser bog beast brethren.\n\n==Quests==\n[[File:Quest point.png|right]] \n{{main|Wetlands quests}}\n\n==Areas of interest==\n[[File:Inv misc idol 05.png|right]]\n===Maps===\n<gallery>\nImage:WorldMap-Wetlands-old.jpg|Map of Wetlands, pre-Cataclysm\nImage:WorldMap-Wetlands.jpg|Map of Wetlands, post-Cataclysm (Current)\n</gallery>\n\n===Elite areas===\nPrior to the [[Cataclysm]], both [[Dun Modr]] and [[Dragonmaw Gates]] were elite areas. Now, however, the former is filled with regular mobs and the latter is now part of the [[Twilight Highlands]].\n\n===Subzones===\n{| class=\"darktable\"\n|-\n!{{wow-inline}} In-game\n|-\n|{{Wetlands|subzonesonly=}}\n|-\n||\n----\n'''Other'''\n\n[[Thandol Valley]] (WC2)\n|}\n{{clrl}}\n\n== In Warcraft III ==\n[[File:Trade_archaeology_highborne_scroll.png|right]] \n{{WC3-section}}\nA Warcraft III map exists called Wetlands. A once thriving [[metropolis]] has all but been covered by the jungle.\n\n== Media ==\n=== Images ===\n;Pre-Cataclysm\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nGrimbatol001.jpg|Grim Batol\nMenethil Harbor.jpg|Menethil Harbor\nDun Modr.jpg|Dun Modr\nWhelgar's Excavation Site.jpg|Whelgar's Excavation Site\nWetlands.jpg|A sunset over the Wetlands.\nWetlandsRain.jpg|Wetlands during the rainy season.\n</gallery>\n\n;Post-Cataclysm\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nFile:Menethil Harbor after Cataclysm.jpg|Menethil Harbor docks\nFile:Menethil Harbor after Cataclysm 2.jpg|Menethil Harbor half-submerged\nFile:Menethil Harbor flooded.jpg|Menethil Harbor flooded\n</gallery>\n\n=== Videos ===\n<gallery position=\"center\" captionalign=\"center\">\nWetlands HD - World of Warcraft Cataclysm\nCataclysm - Wetlands Overview\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Arathi Highlands]]\n* [[Loch Modan]]\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Read http://www.wowwiki.com/WoWWiki:External_links before posting your links here.\nLinks that do not conform to the rules will be DELETED.\nRepeat violations may result in a BAN.\nHave a nice day. :) -->\n{{elinks-zone|11}}\n\n\n{{Wetlands}}\n{{Eastern Kingdoms}}\n\n[[es:Wetlands]]\n[[fr:Les Paluns]]\n[[pl:Wetlands]]\n[[ru:\u0411\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0442\u0438\u043d\u0430]]\n[[Category:Eastern Kingdoms]]\n[[Category:Wetlands| ]]\n[[Category:Dwarf territories]]\n[[Category:Metropolises]]\n[[Category:Jungles]]"}}}